excerpt: Lakeside bird sanctuary with an established trail system known for its domestic & migratory species.
detail_description: Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary in Kerala is a haven for bird enthusiasts, offering a unique opportunity to spot both domestic and migratory species. Spanning across 14 hectares of lush greenery, the sanctuary is home to rare seasonal birds such as Siberian Crane, Night Herons, Pelicans, Parrots, and more. The government ensures the conservation of this natural habitat and its towering coconut trees.
name: Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary
address: Kavanattinkara, Kumarakom, Kerala 686563, India

excerpt: Kumarakom is a village on Vembanad Lake in the backwaters of Kerala, southern India. It’s laced with canals, where houseboats ply the waters. Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary is home to many species including cuckoos and Siberian storks. Nearby, the Bay Island Driftwood Museum displays wooden sculptures. In the lake, Pathiramanal Island is a haven for rare migratory birds. Ancient Thazhathangady Mosque is east of Kumarakom.
detail_description: Kumarakom, a charming village situated on the serene Vembanad Lake in Kerala, India, offers a unique blend of natural beauty and cultural experiences. The area is renowned for its intricate network of canals where traditional houseboats gracefully navigate the waters. Nature enthusiasts will appreciate the Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary, home to diverse bird species including cuckoos and Siberian storks.
name: Kumarakom
address: Kerala, India

excerpt: Sprawling lake with a lush shoreline known for its bird preserve, boating, fishing & festivals.
detail_description: Vembanad Lake is a sprawling body of water with a lush shoreline that is famous for its bird preserve, boating, fishing, and festivals. The area surrounding the lake includes the small lagoon at the East coast under the St. John Nepumseanos Church Shrine near the Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary Observatory Tower. The underwater landscape of this biotope features shallow waters that fill up as the lake level changes, with transparent water and muddy bottoms due to uncontrolled shell mining.
name: Vembanad Lake
address: Kerala

excerpt: A collection of unique driftwood sculptures is displayed at this snug, cylinder-shaped museum.
detail_description: The Bay Island Driftwood Museum is a unique and cozy cylindrical museum that showcases a fascinating collection of driftwood sculptures. The museum promises an enriching experience for history enthusiasts, culture buffs, and curious travelers alike.
name: Bay Island Driftwood Museum

detail_description: Thanneermukkom Bund, located in Kumarakom, Kerala, is a remarkable feat of engineering that serves a crucial role in the area's water management system. This structure effectively separates saline seawater from the freshwater backwaters of Vembanad Lake, preserving the ecological balance. It also provides a picturesque pathway for boats and offers stunning views of the expansive lake and lush surroundings. Additionally, visitors can enjoy activities such as speed boating while taking in the serene atmosphere.
name: Thanneermukkom Bund
address: M9FX+PWG, Vembanad Lake, Kumarakom, Kerala 688527, India

detail_description: The Kumarakom Craft Museum is a must-visit attraction for those interested in rare and unique collections. It features a diverse range of antique items including woodwork, paintings, decorative pieces, sacred figurines, handcrafted Kathakali Dance masks, and more that showcase Kerala's culture and traditional art forms. One of its most prized exhibits is a landscape painting created with strands of hay on black cloth.
name: Travancore Heritage Museum ( Aka Kumarakom craft museum )
address: Craft Museum, PO, Cheepunkal, Kavanattinkara, Kumarakom, Kerala 686563, India

excerpt: Serene 16th-century Hindu temple known for its traditional Kerala-style architecture & murals.
detail_description: Thirunakkara Sree Mahadeva Temple is a serene 16th-century Hindu temple located in the heart of Kottayam, Kerala. It is known for its traditional Kerala-style architecture and vibrant murals depicting themes from Hindu epics. Dedicated to Lord Shiva, this ancient temple was constructed by Thekkumkoor Maharaja and is believed to be nearly 500 years old.

detail_description: Nestled within the enchanting Kumarakom Lake Resort, Ettukettu Specialty Restaurant is a culinary gem that beautifully marries history and gastronomy. Originally built as a gift from King Marthanda Varma to his martial arts instructor, Ettukettu has been thoughtfully relocated to serve as a hub for exquisite dining experiences.

excerpt: Ancient temple known for its murals, gold elephants & an annual 10-day festival in February & March.
detail_description: Ettumanur Shri Mahadeva Temple, located in Kottayam district, is a well-known ancient Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva. Managed by the Travancore Devaswom Board, the temple hosts an annual Arattu festival in February or March that attracts many visitors. The Thulabharam ritual and "Ezharaponnana," featuring seven big and one small golden elephants, are other notable features of this temple.
name: Ettumanoor Shri Mahadeva Temple
address: Ettumanoor Temple Rd, Ettumanoor, Kerala 686631, India
